The Health Economics and Data Analytics (HEDA) Discipline and WA Country Health Services (WACHS) are investing to further strengthen WA country research and innovation opportunities. The Curtin team are at the forefront of health economics and data analytics research and are international leaders in their respective fields.

This role is a funded through a collaboration between WA Country Health Service and Curtin University, this position will support the work of the collaborative in increasing research capacity that focuses on supporting clinical and health professional teams to deliver high-quality, impactful services for rural and remote WA. The focus of the research outputs include: the identification and impact of variation in population and clinical practice; the effectiveness and cost effectiveness of health care interventions; evaluating the development and implementation of models of care.

We are seeking a Senior Research Officer to provide research, administration and technical support to the HEDA and WACHS research partnership.

In this role you will:

Support the development of research concepts and research project proposals in consultation with Project Leads;
Manage project activities and deliverables and liaise with project partners and participants to facilitate outcomes;
Use quantitative and/or qualitative methods to analyse sophisticated data sets, interpret experimental results, and document findings;
Prepare content for research documentation, which may include research grant/funding applications, ethics proposals, research papers and conference presentations;
Participate in the conduct of research activities/experiments;
Collate, review and summarise literature search information.

Why choose Curtin?

An innovative, scientifically stimulating University, with close connections to public and private health organisations;
A nurturing and supportive environment that focuses on supporting early career researchers and teachers to reach their full potential;
Easily accessible location with great parking, bus station and end of trip facilities;
A vibrant campus with gym, child care, wellness programs, medical and counselling services;
We are ranked in the top 1% of universities worldwide (ARWU 2018 and QS World University Rankings 2019).

For further information on Curtin and all of our employee benefits visit https://about.curtin.edu.au/jobs/

You will bring to this role…(selection criteria):

Completion of a Masters and/or PhD in a health sciences or similar discipline and considerable relevant experience; or an equivalent combination of relevant experience and/or education/training;
Strong analytical skills, with the capability to interpret qualitative and quantitative data including large and complex health data sets, interpret experimental results and document findings;
Excellent stakeholder engagement with the ability to coordinate project activities and liaise with project partners and participants to facilitate project outcomes;
Knowledge of research processes and experience preparing content for research documentation, which may include research grant/funding applications, ethics proposals, research papers and conference presentations;
The capacity to participate in the conduct of research activities/experiments/field trips in accordance with the skills required of the position;
Collate, synthesise, review and summarise information from literature searches;
Knowledge/understanding of the healthcare system and a commitment to research within the rural and remote regions of WA would be desirable.

